<li>Element category: metalloid</li>
<li>Electron configuration: 3d10 4s2 4p2</li>
<li>Per shell: 2, 8, 18, 4</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Physical properties</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Phase: solid</li>
<li>Melting point: 1211.40 K ​(938.25 °C, ​1720.85 °F)</li>
<li>Boiling point: 3106 K ​(2833 °C, ​5131 °F)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>History</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Prediction: Dmitri Mendeleev (1871)</li>
<li>Naming: after Germany, homeland of the discoverer</li>
<li>Discovery: Clemens Winkler (1886)</li>
</ul>
